start.label: tell someone where to shove it

examples.en: Extremes meet.
She went on an extreme diet.
A man is in extreme want of food or clothing.
It cools with extreme slowness.
In fact, the truth lies between the two extremes.
They are living in extreme poverty.
We must proceed with extreme caution.
He professed extreme regret.
The plan was rejected as too extreme.
He was hospitalized for extreme fatigue.
This would be running into a very absurd extreme.
He was dressed in the extreme of the English fashion.
The plant is sensitive to extreme heat and cold.
He knew that he was in extreme peril.
He was admired for his extreme piety.
The winds are of extreme heat and aridity.
Clark had become more extreme in his opinions.
The weakness of extreme old age crept upon her.
Force is only justified in extreme circumstances.
He has extreme opinions when it comes to politics.
He was well-known for his extreme political views.
His resentment took the form of extreme hostility.
The roads are slippery: drive with extreme caution.
This kind of experiment seems cruel in the extreme.
The bacteria can withstand extremes of heat and cold.
It is necessary to use extreme caution with chemicals.
The economy reflated after the Fed took extreme measures.
Extreme care is always needed when flying at high speeds.
He had extreme difficulty getting hold of the ingredients.
She suffered extreme embarrassment at not knowing how to read.
